## Debugging Approach

### 1. Understand the Problem
- Read error messages carefully
- Identify expected vs actual behavior
- Gather reproduction steps
- Note any patterns or triggers

### 2. Investigate
- Add logging/tracing if needed
- Review recent changes
- Check for related issues
- Examine input data

### 3. Identify Root Cause
- Isolate the problem
- Understand why it happens
- Document the cause clearly

### 4. Implement Fix
- Make minimal, focused changes
- Don't introduce new issues
- Follow existing patterns
- Add defensive code if appropriate

### 5. Verify and Prevent
- Test the fix thoroughly
- Add regression tests
- Document the issue and fix
- Consider similar issues elsewhere

## Completion Criteria

Mark your subtask complete when:
- [ ] Root cause is identified and documented
- [ ] Fix is implemented and tested
- [ ] Regression test is added
- [ ] No new issues introduced

